[Addendum to above from the New York State West Nile Virus Update - Posted:
August 10, 2000
<http://www.health.state.ny.us/nysdoh/westnile/update/today.htm>

Today, the New York State Health Department's Wadsworth Laboratory reported
22 additional West Nile virus positive birds: New York City, 2 (Manhattan
1, Staten Island 1); Onondaga County, 1; Rockland County, 8; Schenectady
County, 3; Suffolk County, 6; Sullivan County, 1 and Westchester County, 1.
Nine positive mosquito pools were identified: New York City, 3 (Manhattan,
1; Queens 1; Staten Island, 1); Suffolk County, 1 and Westchester County, 5.
Note: the Sullivan County bird is the first documented positive finding in
that county.
The total number of West Nile positive specimens for New York State this
year is 155 birds, 60 mosquito pools and 1 human case. - Mods. JW/CP
