New West Nile virus cases (avian) in Upstate New York
------------------------------------------------------
ROTTERDAM: Two blue jays and a crow infected with West Nile virus [have
been found in Schenectady County. Schenectady County residents who
gathered for a meeting Thursday night, the night before three Capital
Region counties [intended to begin spraying insecticide in neighborhoods
where dead crows [had been found found with West Nile virus, were told 3
more infected birds had turned up - bringing the county's total to 5.
